1
00:00:01,453 --> 00:00:03,413
Previously
on Captain Tsubasa...

2
00:00:03,413 --> 00:00:06,003
Meiwa's team captain,
Kojiro Hyuga,

3
00:00:06,028 --> 00:00:08,268
burst into Nankatsu's
training match

4
00:00:08,293 --> 00:00:10,113
to challenge
star goalkeeper

5
00:00:10,138 --> 00:00:11,428
Genzo Wakabayashi...

6
00:00:11,453 --> 00:00:13,357
and to show off
his skills.

7
00:00:13,382 --> 00:00:14,793
After his teammates
criticized him

8
00:00:14,818 --> 00:00:16,590
for his aggressive
playing style...

9
00:00:16,615 --> 00:00:19,413
Hyuga decided not to
play in the last game...

10
00:00:19,413 --> 00:00:21,992
and told his teammates
to win without him.

11
00:00:22,036 --> 00:00:25,083
In addition, Wakabayashi
suffered a leg injury...

12
00:00:25,714 --> 00:00:27,123
and will not
be able to play

13
00:00:27,148 --> 00:00:29,484
until he has
completely recovered.

14
00:00:29,879 --> 00:00:32,299
Thanks to Tsubasa
and his teammate's efforts,

15
00:00:32,324 --> 00:00:33,855
Nankatsu was
able to advance

16
00:00:34,123 --> 00:00:36,373
without the help of
goalkeeper Wakabayashi.

17
00:00:36,398 --> 00:00:38,958
What challenges await
this young team?

18
00:00:41,793 --> 00:00:43,631
We are here
for today's elimination game

19
00:00:43,741 --> 00:00:46,371
to see who will represent
Shizuoka Prefecture

20
00:00:46,396 --> 00:00:47,856
in the National
Tournament.

21
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,081
Today's match features

22
00:00:49,106 --> 00:00:51,584
team Nankatsu
versus team Shimada.

23
00:00:51,609 --> 00:00:53,377
Good luck to both teams!

24
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:57,160
Nankatsu, Nankatsu,
we will win!

25
00:00:57,185 --> 00:01:00,103
Shimada, Shimada,
we will triumph!

26
00:01:00,128 --> 00:01:00,683
NANKATSU SC LOCKER ROOM

27
00:01:00,683 --> 00:01:03,283
NANKATSU SC LOCKER ROOM
What? So Genzo's not going to play?

28
00:01:03,283 --> 00:01:03,334
What? So Genzo's not going to play?

29
00:01:03,603 --> 00:01:05,433
Why isn't he, coach?

30
00:01:05,643 --> 00:01:06,603
I'm sorry, boys,

31
00:01:06,603 --> 00:01:09,471
but unfortunately,
Genzo is still injured.

32
00:01:09,683 --> 00:01:10,683
-What?
-What?

33
00:01:11,236 --> 00:01:12,776
Hey, guys, don't you worry.

34
00:01:13,028 --> 00:01:14,408
For now, I'll just rest,

35
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:16,643
but I will be ready to play
in the final match.

36
00:01:16,933 --> 00:01:18,893
Shimada is not
a strong team.

37
00:01:19,289 --> 00:01:21,169
I feel very good
about the match.

38
00:01:21,393 --> 00:01:23,393
I'm sure we can win
without him.

39
00:01:23,773 --> 00:01:26,683
Hey, relax, guys, I'll be
ready to play with you.

40
00:01:27,853 --> 00:01:28,733
Yuzo...

41
00:01:28,955 --> 00:01:31,125
I'm counting on you
to protect the goal.

42
00:01:31,313 --> 00:01:32,353
I know you can do it!

43
00:01:32,523 --> 00:01:34,183
I will!
I won't let you down!

44
00:01:34,673 --> 00:01:35,857
Get better soon, yeah?

45
00:01:36,029 --> 00:01:37,443
All right, get some rest.

46
00:01:37,468 --> 00:01:39,143
You'll see that
we'll defeat Shimada.

47
00:01:39,168 --> 00:01:40,208
You just relax!

48
00:01:40,733 --> 00:01:41,733
Mhm.

49
00:01:42,023 --> 00:01:42,733
SHIMADA ELEMENTARY SOCCER TEAM LOCKER ROOM

50
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:44,993
SHIMADA ELEMENTARY SOCCER TEAM LOCKER ROOM
You have all done a great job so far, kids.

51
00:01:44,993 --> 00:01:45,023
You have all done a great job so far, kids.

52
00:01:45,483 --> 00:01:47,603
But our opponent today
is Nankatsu.

53
00:01:47,603 --> 00:01:49,393
Don't take them
for granted, boys.

54
00:01:49,683 --> 00:01:50,813
-Yes, Coach!
-Yes, Coach!

55
00:01:50,893 --> 00:01:53,313
I don't want any of you
thinking that we can't win.

56
00:01:53,868 --> 00:01:55,368
Remember,
the first thing to do

57
00:01:55,393 --> 00:01:57,683
is study the opposing team
to find their weakness

58
00:01:57,763 --> 00:01:59,158
and exploit it to beat them!

59
00:01:59,183 --> 00:02:00,063
-Yes, Coach!
-Yes, Coach!

60
00:02:00,183 --> 00:02:02,183
Don't worry, we'll give it
everything we've got!

61
00:02:03,083 --> 00:02:08,083
[opening theme]

62
00:03:46,615 --> 00:03:46,659
Episode 11: Surprisingly Difficult Match.

63
00:03:46,659 --> 00:03:48,128
Episode 11: Surprisingly Difficult Match.
The second semifinal match

64
00:03:48,128 --> 00:03:48,199
The second semifinal match

65
00:03:48,199 --> 00:03:49,737
to represent Shizuoka Prefecture

66
00:03:49,909 --> 00:03:51,094
is about to begin.

67
00:03:51,119 --> 00:03:52,949
It's Nankatsu versus Shimada.

68
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:54,949
The Nankatsu boys
are the favorite

69
00:03:54,974 --> 00:03:56,619
coming into today's match.

70
00:03:57,369 --> 00:03:58,659
At the Center Forward
position

71
00:03:58,684 --> 00:04:00,239
we have Tsubasa Ozora,

72
00:04:00,264 --> 00:04:02,042
who led the league
in goals scored

73
00:04:02,067 --> 00:04:05,761
with nine goals over
the course of the season.

74
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:08,789
Also, Goalkeeper
Genzo Wakabayashi

75
00:04:08,814 --> 00:04:12,130
has kept his streak going
with zero goals in six games

76
00:04:12,753 --> 00:04:14,003
and looks to keep going.

77
00:04:14,003 --> 00:04:15,558
However,
due to an injury,

78
00:04:15,583 --> 00:04:17,443
Genzo won't play
in today's match...

79
00:04:17,468 --> 00:04:19,807
and player number 12,
Yuzo Morisaki,

80
00:04:19,832 --> 00:04:21,212
will replace him
in the net today.

81
00:04:21,809 --> 00:04:23,793
The Shimada squad
is known for

82
00:04:23,923 --> 00:04:26,213
their incredible teamwork
and endurance.

83
00:04:26,238 --> 00:04:28,068
Thanks to that,
they are here today.

84
00:04:28,934 --> 00:04:30,234
In the first
semifinal match,

85
00:04:30,543 --> 00:04:32,253
Shimizu advanced
to the final...

86
00:04:32,373 --> 00:04:34,728
thanks to captain
Morimichi Kawakami...

87
00:04:34,753 --> 00:04:35,833
the goalkeeper with
the same stature

88
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:37,768
as Genzo Wakabayashi.

89
00:04:38,006 --> 00:04:39,046
The winner of this match

90
00:04:39,071 --> 00:04:40,941
will move on
to face Shimizu.

91
00:04:40,966 --> 00:04:42,926
Now,
may the best team win!

92
00:04:42,951 --> 00:04:45,411
Wow! We're playing
against Nankatsu!

93
00:04:45,572 --> 00:04:47,402
They look like they're
all great players!

94
00:04:48,043 --> 00:04:49,043
-It's a pleasure to play
-It's a pleasure to play

95
00:04:49,068 --> 00:04:51,068
-against you Team Nankatsu!
-against you Team Nankatsu!

96
00:04:51,293 --> 00:04:53,083
Teppei, what's wrong
with them? I don't get it.

97
00:04:53,213 --> 00:04:54,583
They're very friendly.

98
00:04:57,373 --> 00:04:58,583
Go!

99
00:05:01,298 --> 00:05:02,548
You won't get by me!

100
00:05:03,796 --> 00:05:05,923
Looks like this is
gonna be pretty easy!

101
00:05:06,043 --> 00:05:07,213
Mamoru, look.

102
00:05:09,213 --> 00:05:10,543
But why aren't they moving?

103
00:05:10,713 --> 00:05:12,543
Maybe they don't want
the ball or something.

104
00:05:12,673 --> 00:05:14,423
Well, they don't seem
to care about it.

105
00:05:14,874 --> 00:05:17,083
Hah! Well, that will
make it easier.

106
00:05:18,173 --> 00:05:19,583
Take it, Tsubasa!

107
00:05:19,608 --> 00:05:21,672
Mamoru Izawa
sends a long pass

108
00:05:21,697 --> 00:05:22,947
-to Tsubasa Ozora!
-I got it!

109
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:26,948
The pass is
intercepted by team Shimada.

110
00:05:26,973 --> 00:05:28,053
Now they have
the possession!

111
00:05:28,157 --> 00:05:29,737
Excellent control, Koichi!

112
00:05:29,762 --> 00:05:30,842
-What?!
-No way!

113
00:05:31,058 --> 00:05:32,713
Where did he appear from?

114
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:33,873
Captain!

115
00:05:33,873 --> 00:05:35,148
Koichi Fujisawa

116
00:05:35,173 --> 00:05:36,268
-passes the ball to
-Where do you think

117
00:05:36,293 --> 00:05:37,673
-captain Junichi Nagasaki,
-you're going?

118
00:05:37,698 --> 00:05:39,043
who's streaking
down the field!

119
00:05:39,173 --> 00:05:41,228
Junichi receives
the pass easily.

120
00:05:41,253 --> 00:05:42,253
You'll see!

121
00:05:42,278 --> 00:05:44,145
Now Shimada
is moving down the field.

122
00:05:44,170 --> 00:05:45,793
They're approaching
Nankatsu's goal!

123
00:05:45,793 --> 00:05:47,585
Why're you standing there,
Yuzo?

124
00:05:47,863 --> 00:05:49,963
You have to go for the ball.
Get out of the crease!

125
00:05:49,988 --> 00:05:51,218
Huh?
Yes!

126
00:05:51,243 --> 00:05:53,507
All right!
Get ready for this!

127
00:05:53,717 --> 00:05:54,873
What?!

128
00:05:54,873 --> 00:05:57,348
Junichi Nagasaki
shoots a high lob shot.

129
00:05:57,373 --> 00:05:59,833
The ball's headed
toward Yuzo Morisaki!

130
00:06:01,873 --> 00:06:03,938
Oh, no,
goalkeeper Yuzo hesitated,

131
00:06:03,963 --> 00:06:05,963
and ball is in the back
of the net!

132
00:06:05,988 --> 00:06:07,118
Goal for Shimada!

133
00:06:07,333 --> 00:06:08,833
All right!
I didn't think it'd go in!

134
00:06:08,858 --> 00:06:10,253
-We did it! That's the way
-I can't believe that

135
00:06:10,278 --> 00:06:11,963
-it's done, guys!
-we're beating Nankatsu!

136
00:06:12,173 --> 00:06:14,736
What the heck, goalie?
Are you crazy?!

137
00:06:14,761 --> 00:06:16,058
You couldn't stop
such a lousy shot?!

138
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:17,018
-That's embarrassing.
-Uhh...

139
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:18,833
-You should be punished!
-Sanae, calm down.

140
00:06:18,908 --> 00:06:21,278
Shimada is now winning
1 to nothing...

141
00:06:21,303 --> 00:06:23,975
with a lob shot
from inside the box.

142
00:06:24,503 --> 00:06:25,503
Now Nankatsu will have

143
00:06:25,528 --> 00:06:27,186
a tough battle
ahead of them.

144
00:06:27,301 --> 00:06:29,551
We have a surprising
match on our hands!

145
00:06:29,963 --> 00:06:32,003
I thought Nankatsu was
a strong team.

146
00:06:34,293 --> 00:06:35,503
I'm really sorry.

147
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:38,123
Hmm, relax, don't beat
yourself up, Yuzo.

148
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:39,762
Remember,
we scored nine goals

149
00:06:39,787 --> 00:06:41,167
in our previous matches.

150
00:06:41,373 --> 00:06:42,938
Don't worry,
we'll get this one back.

151
00:06:42,963 --> 00:06:43,833
Relax!

152
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:44,833
Thank you, guys.

153
00:06:45,173 --> 00:06:46,978
We'll show them that
they can't beat us

154
00:06:47,003 --> 00:06:47,923
so easily!

155
00:06:48,043 --> 00:06:49,833
We'll tie the game
in an instant!

156
00:06:50,697 --> 00:06:52,027
Today's
elimination match

157
00:06:52,052 --> 00:06:54,348
between Shimada
and Nankatsu

158
00:06:54,373 --> 00:06:55,912
has taken
an unexpected turn.

159
00:06:56,334 --> 00:06:58,833
No one would've imagined
at this point...

160
00:06:58,858 --> 00:07:02,518
that Shimada had scored
a goal against Nankatsu.

161
00:07:03,731 --> 00:07:05,361
It looks like
it's going to rain.

162
00:07:06,043 --> 00:07:06,293
SAITAMA TOURNAMENT SEMI-FINAL

163
00:07:06,293 --> 00:07:08,973
SAITAMA TOURNAMENT SEMI-FINAL
Semi-finals match of the Saitama Prefecture.

164
00:07:08,973 --> 00:07:09,173
SAITAMA TOURNAMENT SEMI-FINAL

165
00:07:09,233 --> 00:07:09,273
NANBU FC MEIWA FC

166
00:07:09,273 --> 00:07:10,563
NANBU FC MEIWA FC
The referee blows the whistle

167
00:07:10,563 --> 00:07:10,688
NANBU FC MEIWA FC

168
00:07:10,688 --> 00:07:11,883
NANBU FC MEIWA FC
for half time.

169
00:07:11,883 --> 00:07:11,913
NANBU FC MEIWA FC

170
00:07:11,913 --> 00:07:12,829
NANBU FC MEIWA FC
The Nanbu team has the lead,

171
00:07:12,829 --> 00:07:13,103
NANBU FC MEIWA FC

172
00:07:13,314 --> 00:07:14,913
three goals to nothing.

173
00:07:14,938 --> 00:07:16,503
Good job!

174
00:07:16,528 --> 00:07:17,658
What a nightmare.

175
00:07:17,683 --> 00:07:18,840
Captain Hyuga said that

176
00:07:18,963 --> 00:07:21,083
we could win the matches
on our own.

177
00:07:21,418 --> 00:07:23,338
Hmm, you can't win
without me, huh?

178
00:07:23,563 --> 00:07:24,143
Huh?

179
00:07:24,623 --> 00:07:26,753
-Captain!
-Well, what's wrong, guys?

180
00:07:26,922 --> 00:07:27,922
I thought you'd all win

181
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,947
with your lovely
playing style, huh?

182
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:31,867
Captain, don't say that!

183
00:07:31,892 --> 00:07:33,092
You have to play for us!

184
00:07:33,463 --> 00:07:34,923
We can't win without you!

185
00:07:35,043 --> 00:07:36,173
Please, Captain.

186
00:07:36,293 --> 00:07:37,673
-Please, Captain!
-Please, Captain!

187
00:07:38,003 --> 00:07:39,003
All right, I will...

188
00:07:39,293 --> 00:07:40,978
but first,
you must promise me

189
00:07:41,003 --> 00:07:42,753
you will play by my rules.

190
00:07:43,469 --> 00:07:45,043
-What?! You want us to play
-What?! You want us to play

191
00:07:45,068 --> 00:07:46,335
-following your style?
-following your style?

192
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,359
Exactly!

193
00:07:47,712 --> 00:07:49,872
My style has never failed!

194
00:07:50,542 --> 00:07:52,712
Only the strong
deserve to win!

195
00:07:53,292 --> 00:07:54,712
And now,
the second half

196
00:07:54,737 --> 00:07:55,832
is about to begin!

197
00:07:55,832 --> 00:07:59,082
It looks like Meiwa
will make a substitution.

198
00:07:59,712 --> 00:08:00,764
Substitution for Meiwa.

199
00:08:00,789 --> 00:08:04,292
Nakamoto, number 13, out,
Hyuga, number 10, enters.

200
00:08:04,422 --> 00:08:06,712
Seriously?!
Kojiro's going to play?!

201
00:08:06,737 --> 00:08:08,252
He didn't play
in the first half,

202
00:08:08,372 --> 00:08:09,582
but why's he playing now?

203
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,880
Substitution for Meiwa.

204
00:08:10,905 --> 00:08:12,807
Koyama, number 14, out,

205
00:08:12,832 --> 00:08:14,582
Sawada, number 15,
enters the match.

206
00:08:14,712 --> 00:08:17,172
That's great! I'll finally
play alongside Kojiro!

207
00:08:17,962 --> 00:08:20,082
But Captain, Takeshi
is only in fourth grade.

208
00:08:20,107 --> 00:08:20,832
Are you sure?

209
00:08:20,962 --> 00:08:22,872
Why did you put him
in to play with us?

210
00:08:22,872 --> 00:08:24,832
In no time,
you'll understand why.

211
00:08:25,002 --> 00:08:27,582
Takeshi is
a very important weapon.

212
00:08:28,726 --> 00:08:29,766
Let's win this, all right?

213
00:08:30,043 --> 00:08:31,043
Yeah!

214
00:08:31,068 --> 00:08:32,988
The second half
of the elimination match

215
00:08:33,622 --> 00:08:34,922
between Meiwa and Nanbu

216
00:08:34,947 --> 00:08:37,122
to represent
the Saitama Prefecture

217
00:08:37,147 --> 00:08:38,397
is about to begin!

218
00:08:39,022 --> 00:08:41,522
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT, SEMI-FINAL SECOND MATCH NANKATSU SC SHIMADA ELEMENTARY

219
00:08:42,082 --> 00:08:44,372
Teppei Kisugi
takes a shot on goal!

220
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:46,152
Oh, what a shame!

221
00:08:46,177 --> 00:08:48,057
It was a poor shot
from inside the box!

222
00:08:48,082 --> 00:08:49,832
Nankatsu still
doesn't have a goal!

223
00:08:49,857 --> 00:08:50,687
Son of a gun!

224
00:08:50,922 --> 00:08:53,557
Teppei, why didn't you
pass the ball to Tsubasa?

225
00:08:53,582 --> 00:08:54,452
He was in front of the net!

226
00:08:54,546 --> 00:08:56,922
Because I wasn't marked,
so I took a shot!

227
00:08:56,922 --> 00:08:59,252
Show off another day,
man. We're losing by a goal!

228
00:08:59,272 --> 00:08:59,362
SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT, SEMI-FINAL SECOND MATCH NANKATSU SC SHIMADA ELEMENTARY

229
00:08:59,362 --> 00:09:00,892
SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT, SEMI-FINAL SECOND MATCH NANKATSU SC SHIMADA ELEMENTARY
Did you forget the score?

230
00:09:00,892 --> 00:09:01,122
Did you forget the score?

231
00:09:01,147 --> 00:09:02,147
Focus!

232
00:09:03,948 --> 00:09:06,528
Up to now, we've taken
more shots on goal,

233
00:09:06,553 --> 00:09:08,593
and we've had more time
of possession.

234
00:09:08,832 --> 00:09:10,792
Even so,
we still can't score!

235
00:09:11,167 --> 00:09:13,207
I don't get what
they're doing!

236
00:09:13,232 --> 00:09:14,732
It doesn't make sense.

237
00:09:17,002 --> 00:09:17,999
The goalie for Shimada

238
00:09:18,024 --> 00:09:19,564
makes a goal kick
to midfield.

239
00:09:21,002 --> 00:09:22,226
Takeshi Kishida from Nankatsu

240
00:09:22,251 --> 00:09:23,251
intercepts the pass.

241
00:09:25,832 --> 00:09:26,832
Someone get him!

242
00:09:26,962 --> 00:09:29,002
Here comes the tying goal!

243
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:30,167
Guys, go and mark him!

244
00:09:30,422 --> 00:09:31,422
-Okay!
-Okay!

245
00:09:32,397 --> 00:09:33,977
The Shimada club are

246
00:09:34,002 --> 00:09:36,832
known for its defense,
as strong as a brick wall.

247
00:09:36,922 --> 00:09:39,280
Three defenders are
now marking Mamoru Izawa!

248
00:09:39,305 --> 00:09:41,372
Mamoru passes to
Teppei Kisugi!

249
00:09:41,397 --> 00:09:43,307
Teppei gets close
and takes a shot!

250
00:09:43,467 --> 00:09:46,256
Oh, but the goalie
is able to stop the ball!

251
00:09:46,281 --> 00:09:48,091
Nankatsu aren't able
to apply pressure.

252
00:09:48,116 --> 00:09:51,487
The Shimada defense
is too strong for them.

253
00:09:51,792 --> 00:09:53,832
Why don't they pass
the ball to Tsubasa?!

254
00:09:55,897 --> 00:09:57,147
And now,
we have finished

255
00:09:57,172 --> 00:09:58,872
the first half
of the match.

256
00:09:58,897 --> 00:10:00,477
The score is still
1 to nothing

257
00:10:00,502 --> 00:10:01,582
in favor of Shimada.

258
00:10:01,962 --> 00:10:03,897
This is something
we did not think

259
00:10:03,922 --> 00:10:05,002
would be happening.

260
00:10:05,042 --> 00:10:07,069
We are witnessing
a meltdown of Nankatsu,

261
00:10:07,094 --> 00:10:08,594
who haven't been
able to score.

262
00:10:11,332 --> 00:10:13,122
Care to tell me what
you are doing?

263
00:10:13,573 --> 00:10:14,653
Your rhythm is horrible.

264
00:10:14,712 --> 00:10:16,082
It looks like
you're all strangers!

265
00:10:16,422 --> 00:10:18,622
Why don't you follow
Tsubasa's lead?

266
00:10:18,922 --> 00:10:20,832
Well, we've been able
to make good passes

267
00:10:20,832 --> 00:10:22,002
fairly easily.

268
00:10:22,344 --> 00:10:23,897
After breaking
their defense,

269
00:10:23,922 --> 00:10:25,462
I had a clear shot, Coach.

270
00:10:25,962 --> 00:10:28,712
Hmm... I understand
why you feel that way,

271
00:10:28,792 --> 00:10:29,872
but Tsubasa's
the only one who's

272
00:10:30,002 --> 00:10:31,506
supposed to score the goals!

273
00:10:32,147 --> 00:10:32,872
In the second half,

274
00:10:32,897 --> 00:10:34,817
I want all of you to pass
the ball to Tsubasa!

275
00:10:34,872 --> 00:10:36,832
-Understood?
-Yes, sir!

276
00:10:36,872 --> 00:10:37,872
Please, Coach,

277
00:10:37,897 --> 00:10:39,397
will you let me play
in the second half?

278
00:10:40,462 --> 00:10:42,422
No, that won't be necessary.

279
00:10:42,542 --> 00:10:44,082
I'm counting on you,
understood?

280
00:10:44,107 --> 00:10:45,107
Understood!

281
00:10:45,962 --> 00:10:46,962
-Huh?
-Huh?

282
00:10:49,087 --> 00:10:50,377
It's starting to rain.

283
00:10:52,715 --> 00:10:55,730
We've never seen anything
like this before!

284
00:10:55,755 --> 00:10:57,872
Takeshi Sawada,
number 15,

285
00:10:57,897 --> 00:11:00,727
weaves his way between
Nanbu defenders!

286
00:11:00,752 --> 00:11:01,832
For a fourth grade boy,

287
00:11:01,857 --> 00:11:04,517
he has a very impressive
football skill!

288
00:11:04,938 --> 00:11:07,188
I didn't think Takeshi
could play like that!

289
00:11:10,637 --> 00:11:11,927
Kojiro, it's yours!

290
00:11:11,952 --> 00:11:12,796
Takeshi Sawada

291
00:11:12,821 --> 00:11:14,725
crosses the ball to
Kojiro Hyuga,

292
00:11:15,491 --> 00:11:16,922
who is in front
of the goal!

293
00:11:16,947 --> 00:11:18,249
This is impressive!

294
00:11:18,292 --> 00:11:19,872
Both players
have lifted their team

295
00:11:19,872 --> 00:11:22,172
in the second half
to tie the game!

296
00:11:22,197 --> 00:11:23,907
I want everyone
to mark Kojiro!

297
00:11:23,932 --> 00:11:26,762
We won't let them score
any more goals!

298
00:11:29,002 --> 00:11:30,002
-Get him!
-Get him!

299
00:11:32,082 --> 00:11:33,922
Here's my shot!

300
00:11:37,122 --> 00:11:38,622
The ref
blows the whistle

301
00:11:38,847 --> 00:11:39,847
for full time!

302
00:11:39,872 --> 00:11:41,717
The scoreboard
reads 4 to 3!

303
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:42,992
With their dramatic
comeback,

304
00:11:43,122 --> 00:11:44,832
Meiwa will represent
Saitama

305
00:11:44,832 --> 00:11:46,872
at the National
Tournament!

306
00:11:46,897 --> 00:11:48,477
It's all thanks to
superstar captain,

307
00:11:48,712 --> 00:11:49,832
Kojiro Hyuga.

308
00:11:49,962 --> 00:11:51,792
He's definitely
someone to watch out for

309
00:11:51,792 --> 00:11:53,872
in the upcoming
National Tournament!

310
00:11:54,002 --> 00:11:55,922
We'll follow him closely!

311
00:11:59,476 --> 00:12:01,806
Taro Misaki
intercepts the ball!

312
00:12:02,044 --> 00:12:04,294
It seems that Nankatsu
refuse to give up.

313
00:12:04,319 --> 00:12:05,529
Taro advances.

314
00:12:06,162 --> 00:12:07,564
Taro, pass the ball!

315
00:12:08,372 --> 00:12:09,372
Here!

316
00:12:09,502 --> 00:12:11,002
Ah, oh, ugh!

317
00:12:11,122 --> 00:12:12,292
Oh, what a shame!

318
00:12:12,422 --> 00:12:14,347
Hajime Taki can't
control the ball

319
00:12:14,372 --> 00:12:15,462
because of the rain!

320
00:12:15,949 --> 00:12:18,987
It looks like luck
is on our side this time.

321
00:12:22,502 --> 00:12:24,372
Hey!
What're you guys doing?!

322
00:12:24,665 --> 00:12:26,872
The Shimada players
don't look tired.

323
00:12:27,097 --> 00:12:28,807
They've played
several matches.

324
00:12:28,832 --> 00:12:30,872
I don't get why they're
not tired right now.

325
00:12:31,332 --> 00:12:32,332
-Listen, Coach...
-Huh?

326
00:12:32,357 --> 00:12:34,002
Do you think I can see
the scouting report

327
00:12:34,027 --> 00:12:35,027
for Shimada?

328
00:12:35,147 --> 00:12:36,147
Well, yes, here.

329
00:12:37,931 --> 00:12:39,891
No, that's not possible!

330
00:12:40,082 --> 00:12:41,872
Nankatsu
has the ball again!

331
00:12:41,872 --> 00:12:43,292
Izawa receives
the ball easily

332
00:12:43,422 --> 00:12:44,517
-and sends a pass
-Tsubasa!

333
00:12:44,637 --> 00:12:45,347
to Tsubasa!

334
00:12:45,372 --> 00:12:47,060
-Okay! Ah!
-Oh, no!

335
00:12:47,085 --> 00:12:50,310
The ball lands right
in a puddle of water!

336
00:12:52,622 --> 00:12:53,872
According to the report,

337
00:12:54,322 --> 00:12:55,992
Shimada don't attack
very often,

338
00:12:56,017 --> 00:12:57,347
but they don't allow
many goals

339
00:12:57,372 --> 00:12:58,372
scored against them.

340
00:12:58,502 --> 00:12:59,752
Well, what does
all that mean?

341
00:13:00,098 --> 00:13:01,018
In each game,

342
00:13:01,043 --> 00:13:03,623
their opponents attack them
for the whole match.

343
00:13:04,170 --> 00:13:06,202
But Shimada has
a solid defense

344
00:13:06,227 --> 00:13:07,437
to recover the ball,

345
00:13:07,462 --> 00:13:08,928
-and then they make
-Captain!

346
00:13:09,111 --> 00:13:10,861
long passes
to attack the opposition...

347
00:13:11,197 --> 00:13:12,767
to score a lucky goal.

348
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,872
Their strategy is
to counterattack!

349
00:13:14,897 --> 00:13:16,817
So then, Shimada are a...

350
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:20,372
Yes! They specialize in
very strong defense!

351
00:13:20,962 --> 00:13:22,872
Shimada sends
a long pass down field!

352
00:13:22,872 --> 00:13:24,792
Hey, quick, everyone,
get back!

353
00:13:26,962 --> 00:13:29,422
Junichi Nagasaki
takes a shot on goal!

354
00:13:30,962 --> 00:13:31,872
Goal!

355
00:13:31,872 --> 00:13:34,542
Shimada have now scored
their second goal!

356
00:13:34,672 --> 00:13:35,622
Huh?!

357
00:13:35,842 --> 00:13:37,532
We're two goals ahead,
Naoki.

358
00:13:37,557 --> 00:13:39,087
I know, this is like a dream!

359
00:13:39,459 --> 00:13:42,712
Very good!
Now the game is ours, boys.

360
00:13:43,330 --> 00:13:45,540
We never had a player
good enough on the team

361
00:13:45,565 --> 00:13:46,787
to be the goalscorer.

362
00:13:46,812 --> 00:13:48,683
We could never score goals!

363
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,820
That's why we decided that
if we can't score,

364
00:13:51,845 --> 00:13:53,385
we wouldn't allow
anyone to score

365
00:13:53,410 --> 00:13:55,810
a single goal on us!

366
00:13:56,742 --> 00:13:59,492
Our style of play
may be very passive,

367
00:13:59,517 --> 00:14:02,477
but thanks to the hard work
and effort of the team...

368
00:14:02,705 --> 00:14:05,512
the boys have shown
their true capabilities,

369
00:14:05,537 --> 00:14:07,752
and I couldn't be
prouder of them!

370
00:14:08,318 --> 00:14:10,712
The determination
of the Shimada boys

371
00:14:10,737 --> 00:14:12,197
will always prevail!

372
00:14:12,634 --> 00:14:14,548
All right!
This time, we will win!

373
00:14:15,371 --> 00:14:17,331
This is
completely unexpected!

374
00:14:17,792 --> 00:14:20,437
In the first ten minutes
of the second half,

375
00:14:20,462 --> 00:14:23,832
Nankatsu are now losing
2 goals to nothing!

376
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:27,332
No!

377
00:14:27,357 --> 00:14:28,527
We're not losing this match!

378
00:14:29,162 --> 00:14:29,292
CAPTAIN TSUBASA

379
00:14:29,292 --> 00:14:31,832
CAPTAIN TSUBASA
We'll be right back with Captain Tsubasa!

380
00:14:31,832 --> 00:14:34,872
CAPTAIN TSUBASA

381
00:14:37,461 --> 00:14:39,894
AFFILIATION: NANKATSU SC BIRTHDAY: MARCH 12 HEIGHT 158 CM WEIGHT: 45 KG BLOOD TYPE: A

382
00:14:39,919 --> 00:14:40,960
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT, SEMI-FINAL SECOND MATCH NANKATSU SC SHIMADA ELEMENTARY

383
00:14:40,985 --> 00:14:42,429
And we're back!

384
00:14:42,549 --> 00:14:44,649
With fifteen
minutes left in the match,

385
00:14:44,674 --> 00:14:46,444
Nankatsu have
not been able

386
00:14:46,477 --> 00:14:47,737
to break the defense
of Shimada.

387
00:14:48,763 --> 00:14:51,376
Can Nankatsu
score the equalizer?

388
00:14:51,591 --> 00:14:53,486
Listen, Coach!
Please put me in!

389
00:14:53,925 --> 00:14:55,845
We have to counterattack
Shimada!

390
00:14:55,845 --> 00:14:58,238
We have to force them
to break their defense

391
00:14:58,263 --> 00:14:59,363
so they have to attack!
And then--

392
00:14:59,388 --> 00:15:00,588
I won't let you play.

393
00:15:01,305 --> 00:15:03,095
Listen, Genzo,
our objective is

394
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,660
to simply play at
the National Tournament.

395
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:07,526
Our objective is to win.

396
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:09,953
If we can't overcome
this obstacle...

397
00:15:10,355 --> 00:15:12,845
there'll be no way
we can win the tournament,

398
00:15:12,845 --> 00:15:14,765
so therefore,
the best thing...

399
00:15:15,264 --> 00:15:16,764
is to lose
this game already

400
00:15:16,789 --> 00:15:18,169
and avoid the humiliation!

401
00:15:18,211 --> 00:15:19,291
But wait, Coach...

402
00:15:19,844 --> 00:15:20,764
Shimada has returned

403
00:15:20,789 --> 00:15:22,329
to their defensive
formation.

404
00:15:22,444 --> 00:15:24,354
Can Nankatsu get close
to the goal to score?

405
00:15:24,925 --> 00:15:25,975
Oh, Roberto!

406
00:15:26,093 --> 00:15:27,753
Tsubasa won't lose, right?

407
00:15:28,095 --> 00:15:30,240
I don't know.
It's difficult to know.

408
00:15:30,265 --> 00:15:32,345
The whole team must
solve the problem.

409
00:15:32,464 --> 00:15:33,464
What?

410
00:15:33,612 --> 00:15:35,135
They're passing
the ball around

411
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:37,683
trying to break
Shimada's defense, but...

412
00:15:37,708 --> 00:15:38,878
the rain is inhibiting them.

413
00:15:39,425 --> 00:15:40,425
It's the first time

414
00:15:40,555 --> 00:15:42,206
they've played in
these conditions.

415
00:15:42,498 --> 00:15:43,384
Ughhh!

416
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:45,425
Overall,
Nankatsu has better

417
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:47,206
possession of the ball,
but due to the rain,

418
00:15:47,269 --> 00:15:49,635
their speed, balance
and precision

419
00:15:49,660 --> 00:15:50,820
has decreased significantly.

420
00:15:50,923 --> 00:15:53,003
They're now playing
at the same level

421
00:15:53,028 --> 00:15:53,858
as their opponents.

422
00:15:54,331 --> 00:15:57,468
All of this gives Shimada
an advantage in the match,

423
00:15:57,493 --> 00:15:59,183
-and it's a problem.
-Oh...

424
00:15:59,519 --> 00:16:02,030
Worst part is they
stay marked on Tsubasa

425
00:16:02,055 --> 00:16:03,095
so he can't go anywhere.

426
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:04,120
Although...

427
00:16:07,135 --> 00:16:08,555
There goes Tsubasa!

428
00:16:08,580 --> 00:16:09,925
He's looking for space!

429
00:16:09,925 --> 00:16:11,765
He now has it and shoots!

430
00:16:12,005 --> 00:16:13,730
But the ball goes directly

431
00:16:13,755 --> 00:16:14,955
-into the goalie's hands!
-Ah!

432
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:16,320
But the ball slips
through the goalie's hands

433
00:16:16,345 --> 00:16:18,595
and it looks like a goal
for Nankatsu!

434
00:16:19,585 --> 00:16:22,235
But the defense miraculously
deflects the ball!

435
00:16:22,260 --> 00:16:24,055
So Shimada
escapes a danger!

436
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:24,920
Nankatsu are
still scoreless!

437
00:16:25,135 --> 00:16:27,345
-Good job, Naoki!
-Good deflection!

438
00:16:27,475 --> 00:16:29,975
Not even Tsubasa can score.
What will we do?

439
00:16:30,055 --> 00:16:31,055
They've lost.

440
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,370
This is Shimada's game.

441
00:16:34,065 --> 00:16:36,065
Koichi
Fujisawa kicks the ball

442
00:16:36,090 --> 00:16:37,394
and crosses it midfield.

443
00:16:37,419 --> 00:16:39,845
The Nankatsu defenders
chase after it,

444
00:16:39,975 --> 00:16:42,383
but the rain is
slowing them down.

445
00:16:42,408 --> 00:16:44,581
I can't believe it.

446
00:16:46,265 --> 00:16:47,265
-Tsubasa!
-Tsubasa!

447
00:16:47,706 --> 00:16:50,675
We're not going to lose!
Do you hear me?!

448
00:16:52,726 --> 00:16:54,846
Look at
Tsubasa Ozora's tenacity!

449
00:16:55,019 --> 00:16:56,900
It's motivating
his teammates

450
00:16:56,925 --> 00:16:58,401
-as they go on the attack!
-Don't let them get close!

451
00:16:58,426 --> 00:16:59,806
We have to stop them!

452
00:17:01,885 --> 00:17:02,845
Let's focus, guys!

453
00:17:02,845 --> 00:17:04,555
One-touch passes,
you hear me?!

454
00:17:07,335 --> 00:17:08,335
Quickly, Taro!

455
00:17:09,015 --> 00:17:09,845
Go!

456
00:17:09,870 --> 00:17:10,820
Teppei!

457
00:17:10,925 --> 00:17:11,925
Tsubasa!

458
00:17:12,026 --> 00:17:13,736
All together now.
We have to support him!

459
00:17:13,975 --> 00:17:14,975
Yeah!

460
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,360
Incredible!

461
00:17:16,385 --> 00:17:18,175
Nankatsu is making
one-touch passes

462
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,700
and the ball is no longer
getting stuck in the mud!

463
00:17:20,725 --> 00:17:21,725
Good job!

464
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,000
That's how it's done,
Tsubasa!

465
00:17:23,845 --> 00:17:26,675
A football team
isn't just one player.

466
00:17:26,925 --> 00:17:28,515
Control the pace
of the game...

467
00:17:28,540 --> 00:17:29,830
and make them follow you!

468
00:17:30,175 --> 00:17:30,925
Here!

469
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:32,280
Even without Genzo,

470
00:17:32,305 --> 00:17:34,925
if they work as a team,
they can win the match!

471
00:17:35,265 --> 00:17:37,490
Nankatsu
are now on the attack,

472
00:17:37,515 --> 00:17:39,305
and they are near
Shimada's goal!

473
00:17:39,425 --> 00:17:40,725
Tsubasa!

474
00:17:45,765 --> 00:17:47,595
Tsubasa Ozora
jumps wonderfully

475
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:48,792
into the air for
a scissor kick

476
00:17:48,817 --> 00:17:50,527
that's headed toward
the goal!

477
00:17:50,845 --> 00:17:52,765
-Ah!
-Goal!

478
00:17:52,790 --> 00:17:54,750
Thanks to Taro Misaki's
beautiful cross,

479
00:17:54,775 --> 00:17:56,800
Tsubasa put
a powerful shot on goal!

480
00:17:56,825 --> 00:17:58,714
Now they just need
one goal to tie!

481
00:17:58,925 --> 00:18:00,635
-You did it, Tsubasa!
-Yes!

482
00:18:00,660 --> 00:18:01,490
That's how it's done!

483
00:18:01,515 --> 00:18:03,385
Perfect!
Now we need just one more!

484
00:18:03,410 --> 00:18:05,573
That goal
breaks Shimada's record

485
00:18:05,598 --> 00:18:07,425
for most shutouts.
Such a pity!

486
00:18:07,555 --> 00:18:09,475
Relax, guys,
don't worry about it.

487
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:11,910
Will Nankatsu be able to
score the tying goal,

488
00:18:11,935 --> 00:18:14,185
or will Shimada hold out
until the end?

489
00:18:14,539 --> 00:18:16,459
There five minutes left
until the final whistle.

490
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:18,261
Take it, Tsubasa!

491
00:18:19,801 --> 00:18:20,885
Here, Taro!

492
00:18:23,245 --> 00:18:24,245
To you!

493
00:18:24,614 --> 00:18:26,070
Taro Misaki makes

494
00:18:26,095 --> 00:18:27,105
a beautiful cross
to the center!

495
00:18:27,130 --> 00:18:28,340
The ball is mine!

496
00:18:28,925 --> 00:18:29,845
The rain
can't stop them now!

497
00:18:30,614 --> 00:18:32,635
Mamoru Izawa
heads the ball

498
00:18:32,660 --> 00:18:34,260
between two
Shimada defenders

499
00:18:34,285 --> 00:18:35,070
to Tsubasa...

500
00:18:35,095 --> 00:18:37,707
And Tsubasa heads ball
past the goalkeeper!

501
00:18:37,732 --> 00:18:39,762
Goal for Nankatsu!

502
00:18:39,925 --> 00:18:40,925
Nankatsu tie the game

503
00:18:40,950 --> 00:18:42,925
with just a few minutes
left to play!

504
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:44,845
You did it, Tsubasa!

505
00:18:48,709 --> 00:18:50,789
Their team is really strong!

506
00:18:51,175 --> 00:18:52,845
Yes.
It looks like they're

507
00:18:52,845 --> 00:18:54,425
finally showing
their strength.

508
00:18:54,975 --> 00:18:56,175
What should we do now?

509
00:18:56,385 --> 00:18:58,135
Should we continue
to play on defense or what?

510
00:18:58,160 --> 00:18:59,030
-What?
-Well, yeah,

511
00:18:59,055 --> 00:19:00,805
we've always played
like that, Captain.

512
00:19:01,095 --> 00:19:02,425
I think it's
the perfect time

513
00:19:02,450 --> 00:19:04,262
for Nankatsu to see
our true strength.

514
00:19:04,635 --> 00:19:06,515
How about this time we play
on the offense

515
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:08,040
instead of playing
defensively?

516
00:19:08,246 --> 00:19:09,246
-Hm...
-Hm...

517
00:19:09,869 --> 00:19:11,699
You have to get
out of your comfort zone!

518
00:19:12,055 --> 00:19:12,845
-Huh?
-Huh?

519
00:19:12,845 --> 00:19:13,754
Our work as a team

520
00:19:13,779 --> 00:19:15,779
has always been admirable,
right?

521
00:19:15,975 --> 00:19:17,715
We're nobody if we play
individually,

522
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:19,780
but together,
I know we can do it!

523
00:19:20,255 --> 00:19:21,352
If we're going to win,

524
00:19:21,377 --> 00:19:23,417
we have to do it properly,
by attacking!

525
00:19:24,144 --> 00:19:27,234
That way, we will be
honoring our beloved coach!

526
00:19:28,015 --> 00:19:30,515
Let's play football
the Shimada way!

527
00:19:30,765 --> 00:19:31,845
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

528
00:19:33,114 --> 00:19:34,244
Incredible!

529
00:19:34,269 --> 00:19:36,845
Shimada have broken
their line of defense,

530
00:19:36,845 --> 00:19:39,746
and now, they're heading
toward Nankatsu's goal!

531
00:19:39,771 --> 00:19:40,725
-What is this?!
-What is this?!

532
00:19:41,175 --> 00:19:43,135
Nankatsu
don't know what to do

533
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:43,925
about this!

534
00:19:44,055 --> 00:19:46,700
Shimada now has complete
control of the ball

535
00:19:46,725 --> 00:19:47,675
and the pitch!

536
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:48,675
What are you doing?!

537
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:50,725
Don't just stand there.
Mark them!

538
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:51,965
I got it!

539
00:19:52,570 --> 00:19:53,610
All together!

540
00:19:53,775 --> 00:19:56,055
Shimada is now advancing
toward the goal!

541
00:19:56,267 --> 00:19:58,767
What a sight to see them
playing like this!

542
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:01,360
Right now, the match
could go either way!

543
00:20:01,631 --> 00:20:03,631
We'll show them what
Shimada is made of!

544
00:20:03,821 --> 00:20:05,201
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

545
00:20:05,522 --> 00:20:07,392
-They're a great team!
-Mhm!

546
00:20:07,819 --> 00:20:09,439
I feel as though
they enjoy soccer!

547
00:20:10,044 --> 00:20:12,149
So now, I won't
give up either!

548
00:20:12,174 --> 00:20:14,804
Tsubasa tries to take
the ball with a slide tackle.

549
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:17,509
But Shimada maintains
possession and regroups!

550
00:20:17,534 --> 00:20:18,404
No!

551
00:20:18,537 --> 00:20:19,447
That's it!

552
00:20:19,472 --> 00:20:21,975
That's the true
Shimada spirit!

553
00:20:22,595 --> 00:20:25,339
Football is about
working as a team!

554
00:20:25,870 --> 00:20:28,030
We all help each other
like brothers...

555
00:20:28,055 --> 00:20:29,675
on the path to victory!

556
00:20:31,714 --> 00:20:32,714
I can't believe it!

557
00:20:32,739 --> 00:20:34,635
Junichi Nagasaki

558
00:20:34,660 --> 00:20:35,450
-centers the ball
-Naoki!

559
00:20:35,475 --> 00:20:36,649
to Naoki Uesugi,

560
00:20:36,674 --> 00:20:37,794
who is all alone
and unmarked!

561
00:20:41,459 --> 00:20:44,205
And
goalkeeper Yuzo Morisaki

562
00:20:44,378 --> 00:20:45,758
makes a save!

563
00:20:45,783 --> 00:20:47,186
What a nice attempt!

564
00:20:47,211 --> 00:20:48,211
Good, Yuzo!

565
00:20:48,845 --> 00:20:50,739
Yes, Genzo!
I can do it!

566
00:20:51,123 --> 00:20:53,675
The goalkeeper
fires a long kick...

567
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:55,450
launching Nankatsu's
counterattack!

568
00:20:55,563 --> 00:20:57,143
Everybody, get back,
quickly!

569
00:20:57,317 --> 00:20:59,475
Number 10
has the ball for Nankatsu!

570
00:20:59,595 --> 00:21:00,595
-He's going straight
-It's mine!

571
00:21:00,620 --> 00:21:01,475
for the goal!

572
00:21:01,595 --> 00:21:03,385
Shimada can't
catch up to him!

573
00:21:04,315 --> 00:21:06,895
Now it's Tsubasa
against the goalie!

574
00:21:08,719 --> 00:21:10,509
Goal!

575
00:21:14,725 --> 00:21:17,015
And the referee blows
the final whistle!

576
00:21:17,135 --> 00:21:18,055
Yeah!

577
00:21:18,175 --> 00:21:20,175
Nankatsu is victorious!

578
00:21:20,305 --> 00:21:22,055
They were able to
erase the deficit,

579
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:23,960
and now they have
advanced to final!

580
00:21:24,496 --> 00:21:27,925
Nankatsu will now face
Shimizu in the final,

581
00:21:28,055 --> 00:21:29,515
and the winner
will represent

582
00:21:29,540 --> 00:21:31,130
the Shizuoka Prefecture.

583
00:21:31,515 --> 00:21:32,845
With his last goal,

584
00:21:32,870 --> 00:21:34,925
Tsubasa has now scored
hat tricks

585
00:21:34,925 --> 00:21:37,595
in six consecutive
matches!

586
00:21:38,736 --> 00:21:39,736
Good job!

587
00:21:47,832 --> 00:21:50,175
Great job today, boys.

588
00:21:51,135 --> 00:21:53,055
Hey, guys, don't be sad!

589
00:21:53,475 --> 00:21:55,650
We gave it all we had
against Nankatsu.

590
00:21:55,675 --> 00:21:56,885
We should be proud of that!

591
00:21:57,425 --> 00:21:59,595
We were a worthy and
resilient opponent!

592
00:22:01,559 --> 00:22:03,635
-Thanks for a great game!
-Thanks for a great game!

593
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:06,030
It was really fun playing!

594
00:22:06,055 --> 00:22:07,746
-Good luck in the final!
-Thank you!

595
00:22:07,771 --> 00:22:10,225
-I hope we play again!
-Yeah, me too!

596
00:22:10,345 --> 00:22:11,780
Well, we're counting
on you guys

597
00:22:11,805 --> 00:22:13,885
to represent our city
with dignity, all right?!

598
00:22:13,910 --> 00:22:15,080
We won't let you down!

599
00:22:16,095 --> 00:22:17,765
Shimada today
gave us a lesson

600
00:22:17,790 --> 00:22:19,395
to work as a team.

601
00:22:19,820 --> 00:22:22,480
They made us see
what our team needs...

602
00:22:22,711 --> 00:22:23,961
what we have to do.

603
00:22:24,749 --> 00:22:27,579
Hey, Tsubasa, now we just
have to win the final!

604
00:22:28,055 --> 00:22:29,055
Yeah.

605
00:22:29,425 --> 00:22:30,225
Now...

606
00:22:30,345 --> 00:22:32,765
together, we will win
the final!

607
00:22:32,885 --> 00:22:35,175
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

608
00:22:36,415 --> 00:22:41,415
[ending theme]
